FBIS3-44028 "drafr015_d_94021" FBIS-AFR-94-015 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Lesotho More Shooting Noted in Maseru 21 Jan; Events Detailed Troops Attack Defense Headquarters MB2301092194 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 0900 GMT 23 Jan 94 MB2301092194 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] South Africans have been advised not to travel to Maseru or its surrounding areas because of the renewed fighting between rival Lesotho military factions which broke out there this morning. Diplomats say it is difficult to obtain a clear picture of what is happening, but troops from the Makoanyane Barracks on the outskirts of the capital are believed to have launched an attack on the defense force headquarters in Maseru. South African Foreign Minister Pik Botha is being kept well informed on the situation.
